  "prompt": "In SimCity BuildIt, how important is it to build the airport?",
  "response": "In SimCity BuildIt, building the airport is quite important for a few reasons:\n\n1. **Trade and Resources**: The airport allows you to send and receive planes carrying trade shipments. This can help you acquire rare materials and goods that are essential for building and upgrading structures in your city.\n\n2. **Expansion of City**: With the airport, you can unlock access to new regions and expand your city\u2019s boundaries, increasing your overall area for development and resources.\n\n3. **Visitor Attractions**: Having an airport attracts more visitors to your city, which can lead to increased revenue and a boost in your city's population.\n\n4. **Delivery of Goods**: The airport offers a way to expedite the delivery of goods. This is especially useful if you're trying to fulfill orders quickly or participate in events that require timely deliveries.\n\nOverall, while it might take time and resources to build the airport, its benefits in terms of trade, expansion, and overall city management make it a valuable addition to your city in SimCity BuildIt.",
